inn1.comm: good ball, on target, some movement off the pitch, Gilchrist works that to the onside, but no chance of a run
good ball again, a good length on the stumps, again Gilchrist stands and works that to midwicket
pace and bounce outside the off stump, Gilchrist chases it leaden-footed and gets beaten, that ball flew through to McCullum
changes his length and pitches that right upto him, Gilchrist wasn't expecting it and drives that to mid-off
short of a length outside off stump, Gilchrist pushes that into the covers and sets off, Australia are on the board
a fullish ball outside the off stump, some movement away, and Watson's comfortable just shouldering arms
from over the wicket, lands on a shortish length and Gilchrist defends to cover
this one's wide of off stump and Gilchrist goes for the cut, but gets beaten by the carry on that ball, if he'd hit that it would have raced away
lands on middle and leg and moves away, Gilchrist stands and defends to the off side
angled across him and he stands up and runs that down to third man
a bouncer, quick and sits up off the deck, forces Watson to duck out of harm's way, good pitch this

lands on a good length outside off stump and moves in sharply, Watson tries to tickle that fine but can't time it well, ball trickles to the onside and Marshall from square leg swoops in and fields, good over from Bond
lands on a good length on and moves in, but Gilchrist's on top of it, pushes that to cover and calls for the run, Watson responds in a flash

he's gone! Tamest dismissal I've seen in a while! Pitched on a short of a good length on off stump, Watson goes for an ugly attempt at a pull shot but doesnt time it at all, ball just balloons up ever so slowly to mid-off and Fulton takes it, first blood for New Zealand
full outside off stump, Ponting gets a stride forward and shoulders arms
full on off stump, Ponting gets onto it and drives that to mid-on, off the mark

gone! Mills! Pitches on a good length on leg stump, ball stops on him and all he can do is work that off the hips towards midwicket, where Oram dives forward and plucks it as it dips, another tame shot from an Australian and this side's been rocked
full on the stumps, he gets behind the ball and defends to cover
full outside off stump, again Ponting gets a stride forward and shoulders arms
full again, and again he leaves it alone
moving down leg, he tries to flicks but cant time it well

reverse-swinging yorker! Full and fast, Ponting comes forward and gets hit smack on the toe, everyone appeals but Bucknor shakes his head, that laned outside off, unfortunately for Bond, but what swing on that ball
full and swinging again, Ponting lunges forward and defends, gets an inside edge&
fuller on middle and off, he comes forward and flicks past square leg, a much more controlled shot, but another super over
full outside off stump, left alone with a stride forward&
short of a good length on the stumps, Ponting goes back in solid defence
good length ball outside off stump and moving in, no room to drive or cut, and again Ponting's forced to go back and defend
drops this a tad shorter and allows Ponting the option of driving off the backfoot in the gap at cover for a quick single
fullish and seaming away, Martyn defends away from his body but keeps that along the ground to point
full outside the off stump, he shoulders arms
a straight delivery outside the off stump, Ponting gets forward and defends, ball rolls to point, loud call of 'NO' from Ponting to Martyn
lands outside off stump and moves in sharply, Ponting allows it to come onto him and plays that with soft hands in front of square leg for a good single
movement off the pitch! Fullish length outside off stump and jags in a mile and a half, Martyn leaves it alone and McCullum collects
lands outside off stump on a shortish length and comes in again, this time Martyn hops and chops that to backward point
comes in again, Martyn beaten for pace and bounce, ball catches him high on the kneel roll, but pitched outside off and was carrying over the stumps, ball rolls to the offside and they pinch a run
full outside off stump, left alone
full on middle and leg, flicked to Franklin at square leg
pitches on a good length outside off stump, Martyn stands and presents the full face of the bat
lands on a good length and comes in, turned to Vettori at midwicket, no chance of a run again
a tad shorter on off stump, he again hops and works that to midwicket
full and he's drawn into a one-handed drive, beaten all ends up, well bowled, sloppy shot

full again, but this time he just presents the full face of the bat and pushes that between the stumps and mid-on, perfectly placed and he gets four even as Vettori  gives chase from mid-on, superb shot
full outside off stump and moving in, Ponting comes forward and drives, gets an inside edge back onto the front pad
too wide outside off stump and swinging the other way, wide signalled
full and moving away again, not that wide though, and Ponting gets a big stride forward and shoulders arms
lands outside off stump and moves in, catches Ponting on the hop, he's struck on the back leg moving across the stumps, a loud appeal from all but that was outside the line, what swing from this man
too wide down the pads, ball swung like something and screached into McCullum's gloves
full outside off stump, Martyn wants nothing to do with it
short and wide, a bad ball from Bond, and Martyn duly smacks that over point for four, he has so much time this batsman, a gem to watch

but this is BOND, and he follows up with a ripper that swings in from outside off stump and cuts Martyn in half, he falls over and the ball somehow misses slicing him open, this is top-class cricket we're viewing here
pitches on a good length on off stump, Ponting goes right back and defends, his head comes down in solid concentration
pitched up too much, and Ponting walks into a wonderfully-placed straight drive that screams down the turf for four
shortish and going down leg, Ponting hops and works that off the hips for one
good length ball outside off stump, Martyn hops and defends that to mid-on
drifts down the legs and he clips that down to Bond at fine leg
wide of offstump and lifting, he shoulders arms for McCullum to collect
too full outside off stump, he thought about cutting that away but left it alone, and its called wide by Bucknor
better, an awkward length and very fast, and Martyn can only defend
short and rising outside the off stump, Martyn sways back and the ball speeds away over McCullum and down to the ropes for four, a wide called as well, express delivery though
short and lifting outside off stump, an its called wide again, Bond not happy, looking at Bucknor, he can feel cheated on the last delivery, but not this time
fullish outside off stump, Martyn's suckered into a drive and gets beaten
full again, this time he gets a stride forward and shoulders arms
strives for the yorker but its too full on the legs, clipped down to deep backward square leg where Mills comes around and fields, an easy two for the batsmen
full outside off stump, shoulders arms again
full once more, this time he times the forward push well in the gat at cover and picks up two, placed
full outside off stump, Ponting comes forward and defends, ball thuds into the pads, Mills lets out a muted appeal, ball clearly outside the line
a fraction shorter outside the off stump, ball didnt sit up that much, and Ponting attempts an ambitious pull across the line but cant even touch the ball
full and moving away outside off stump, he gets a huge stride forward and shoulders arms
full outside off stump again, but this time he gets that huge stride to the pitch of the ball and drives that on the up past cover-point for four, good shot

and we have another awesome reply from the bowler! Lands on a sweet length on off stump, some seam movement away, and Ponting's caught coming forward, ball just misses the edge of the bat as it carries on
lands on a good length on the stumps, Ponting goes back and defends
from over the wicket, lands on a shortish length, Martyn stands and defends
a tad shorter and moving away from Martyn, who stands and chops that past backward point, Fulton comes around from third man and fields on the ropes
this lands on leg stump and jumps into Ponting's ribs, sputtered into him as he tried to flick, and he's hurting now
fuller on middle and leg, he comes forward and drives that to Vettori at mid-on
full on off stump, Ponting comes forward and drives to mid-off this time
short ball moving across him, he's tucked for room and cant time the cut, ball runs straight to cover
lands on a good length outside off stump, Martyn stands and keeps that down in front of point with solid technique
half-tracker outside off stump, bread and butter for WACA-bred Martyn, who stands and slaps that past a diving Vincent at point for four, easy as, oh...you know what I mean
he oversteps this time, wasnt a bad ball but you cant be doing that
too short on middle and off and he puts this away with an authoritative pull through midwicket, four more and its the 50 for Australia
better ball on a good length outside off, this time Martyn gets his head down and defends
well bowled, lands outside off and lifts sharply and Martyn's caught chasing
full outside off stump and Martyn shoulders arms with a stride forward
full on off stump, Ponting pushes that to mid-off and calls for the run early, and gets it too
short on middle and leg, sits up and catches Martyn hopping, but its a no ball, poor cricket
moving away from middle and off, Martyn drives airily and gets a thick outside edge down to Fulton at third man
lands on middle and off and moves past him, he gets across the stumps but then watches it like a hawk through to McCullum
more middle and leg and moving into him, Ponting defends to midwicket
too full and he just gets forward and drives that between the nonstriker and the stumps, moves into the drive with awesome balance, and the ball speeds away for four
dropped in halfway down the track and Ponting slams the pull down to the deep backward square leg ropes, super shot
full on off stump, Martyn flicks to mid-on
good length on the stumps, Martyn stands and drops the hands, ball rolls to the onside where Oram picks up in his followthrough
full outside off stump, he lets it go with ease
full outside off stump, he gets forward and defends
lands on a good length outside off stump and this time Martyn stands and defends
another good ball outside off stump, Martyn stands and defends with soft hands
looped up outside off stump, Ponting leaves it alone
tossed up again, Ponting gets a stride forward and defends
just a fraction shorter and Ponting goes back and cuts,  but right to backward point
tossed up, good loop, draws Ponting forward in defence again, well bowled&
tossed up outside off stump, Ponting easily onto the front foot and drives down to Bond at long-off
a little flatter on this occasion, Martyn comes forward and defends
full outside off stump, driven wide of point for one
short and wide, he cuts that in the gap at gully for one to third man
back of a good length outside off stump, Ponting defends that to Vincent at point
lands on a good length and draws him forward, he pokes and gets a thick edge down to third man
slow and full outside off stump, Martyn comes onto the front foot and defends to point
full and straight, Martyn gets forward and pushes that back to Oram
tossed up, Ponting comes forward and drives to cover
holds his length, Ponting goes forward and then back, drives to point
tossed up again, Martyn gets half-forward and defends, ball rolls to the onside
tossed up invitingly, Martyn gets forward and drives that loosely to Fleming at cover
tossed up wider outside off stump, left alone
length's a fraction shorter and Martyn tries the late dab but cant beat Vincent diving from gully
lands outside off stump and seams in, raps Ponting on the front foot as he defends, a big shout but not-out says the umpire, looked to have been moving down leg, but a good shout
shorter and moving in, he runs that off the face of the bat to third man for one
a good length on the stumps, defended off the front foot
short of a length on the stump, turned past square leg and they set off, Bond's slow coming around from fine leg and they steal two
changed his pace on that one outside off stump, Martyn stands and defends to point
this time he bounces him, Martyn gets down on his haunches
tossed up, Ponting gets forward and drives with soft hands past point for one
looped up, Martyn comes forward and defends, wants the run but no says Ponting

gone! Tossed up on the stumps, Martyn gets forward and tries to sweep, doesnt read the arm ball and he's caught on the front pad, looked to be hitting leg stump and Bucknor doesnt  take long to raise the finger, Vettori strikes
from around the wicket to the leftie, floated up teasingly outside off stump and sucks Hussey into a forward prod, beats him
flatter this time outside off stump and Hussey gets forward and defends to point
pitches on middle and leg and he comes down and flicks, but only finds Fleming at midwicket
good length outside off stump, Ponting goes back and defends
full outside off stump, he gets forward and defends with a loud 'NO' to Hussey
just a fraction shorter outside off stump, Ponting moves into the pull but gets a top-edge over slips for four, he wanted to heave that over midwicket!
slower on a good length, Ponting hops and turns that to the on side
good ball lands on middle and off and moves away past him, Hussey lets it through to McCullum, but thought about poking at it&
moves across him and then cuts back close to off stump, but he obviously knows where it is as he shoulders arms
tossed up on the stumps, Ponting comes forward and defends
quicker this time, draws him forward again
holds its line and comes onto him slower, but he's on top of it
tossed up on the legs, worked to midwicket
tossed up on middle and leg, Ponting sweeps and gets one around the corner as Oram is late on it
fired into middle and off, Hussey comes forward and chips that to mid-on for one, sharp running that
good ball on off stump, Hussey stands and drops the hands on it, thinks about the run to cover but resists
short of a length outside off stump, he runs that down to third man
on a good length on off stump, Ponting gets a stride forward and turns that magnificently around the corner for four, well flicked down to fine leg
dropped in shorter and he gets a stride forward and heaves that across the line aggressively, but its just one down to Astle on the deep midwicket ropes
Almost! Full and he slams that just over Vettori at mid-off, who jumps high in the air and manages to get his fingertips to it, but the ball grazes them and carries on for four, too close for comfort
lands on middle and leg and its eased around the corner for one
wide of off stump and he allows it to pass
full and slower, sucks Hussey into a loose drive in the air but it lands safely in front of mid-off

good shout! Lands on the stumps and carries on, raps him on the knee roll plumb in front of middle stump, Franklin appeals but Bucknor shakes his head, what the hell was wrong with that appeal? AND the batsmen steal a legbye! Unlucky Franklin, there's no excuse for those
full on middle and off, driven back to Franklin
angles away from off stump and he tries a square drive, wide signalled
full and slower, driven to mid-off for one
full on the pads, flicked to Astle at deep midwicket, Ponting wants two but Hussey say no as the throw comes in quickly
a good length outside off stump, Ponting opens the face and runs that down to third man for one more

short of a length and moving across him, Hussey too opens the face of the bat and runs that to third man, Hussey thinks about the second but McCullum fields the throw and fires down to the nonstrikers end, ball hits the stumps, they go upstairs but is decided he was safely in
full outside off stump and rising, Ponting shoulders arms coming forward
short outside off stump, slower ball, he goes back and defends to cover airily
short of a good length again, Ponting rocks back and defends to point
good length, comes forward and drives back to Oram
banged in short, on the middle, Hussey rocks back and pulls through the midwicket region
fuller, on the middle and leg, Hussey goes back to nudge it for a single on the on side
100 is up with a lovely off drive. Ponting eases forward to caress a fullish-delivery on the off and middle stump line straight down the ground.
And again. He lunges forward to a slightly overpitched delivery on the middle, and punch-drives it between the bowler and mid-on.
slanted delivery, Ponting is hit on the pads as he pushes forward in defense
Pushes a length-delivery to the off side, wants a run, Ponting is also interested but both decide against it as the fielder swoops in from cover
slightly slower, slightly wide outside off, Hussey reaches out for it to skew it towards cover
on a length, angling away, dabbed down the thirdman. Ponting on strike, he is on 49
Ponting gets his 55th ODI fifty with a push towards cover. Hares down the track to bring up his ninth fifty against New Zealand.
length-delivery on the middle, Hussey gets behind the line and dead-bats it away
short and outside off, cut past cover
turns away after landing on a length outside the off stump, Ponting goes back to cut it to deep point
after two looseners Vettori gets it right this time. Flighted delivery, just short of driveable length, turns in from the offstump line, pushed back down the track
lands on the middle, turns down leg, nudged to the on side
fuller, on the middle, driven down the ground
slightly short, just outside off, Hussey goes back to tap it to left of Oram at short thirdman, will get a single.
starts off with a long-hop, Hussey's eyes light up, and he swivels to pull it away easily in front of square
on the legs again, tickled down to fine-leg
leans forward to push a length-delivery outside off to right of cover
Again lunges forward, pushes it to mid-on, wants a run, Hussey responds before Ponting sends him back quickly as he sees Vettori rushing on to the ball
Overpitched and Ponting jumps on to it in a flash, drills it down the ground

Huge wicket! Ponting is gone. Out playing a pull shot. Mills gets the breakthrough in the first over of his second spell. It landed on a length, outside the off stump, jumped up a bit and Ponting tried to fetch it around from there, made contact with the toe-end of the bat and shoveled it across to Vettori at mid-on
driven to right of Vincent at midwicket who gets across quickly to make a diving stop.
turns in from outside off, pushed to cover point
swept from outside off. They hare down the track to come back for a second
defended off the front foot
tossed up on the off, turns in slightly, Hussey is rapped on the pads as he pushes forward in defense
greets Symonds with a bouncer. Banged in well short, ducked under without too much fuss
length-delivery outside off, keeps a touch low, Symonds lets it go through to 'keeper
in the zone outside off, left alone
again pings the channel outside off, again left alone by Symonds. A yorker now won't be a bad idea.
he opts for the nip-backer, the one that comes back in after pitching on a length around the off stump line. Symonds pushes forward to keep it out

lovely delivery to finish the over off. Again the one that darts back in but much pronounced movement this time. Hisses back in after landing outside the off stump and goes through Symond's tentative poke and raps him on the thigh.
Perfume ball first up. Hussey sways away quickly. 83.0mph delivery.
Around that 84mph delivery again, but fuller and outside off, pushed past point
Edges to the thirdman boundary.  The one that held its line after landing on a length around the off stump, Symonds pushed at it with soft hands, plays inside the line a bit but gets a fruitful edge
in the zone outside off, left alone
84.8 mph delivery, on the middle and leg, nudged around the corner for a single
on the legs, tickled behind square -leg, McCullem sets off in pursuit, Vettori rushes in from long-leg but by then they complete two, Very well-placed by Hussey.
The mid-on and mid-off is up. Tempting Symonds to go over. However Vettori starts off with a slightly shorter one outside off, cut away past point
floated up on the offstump line, turns away, Symonds leans forward to push it to cover
With the mid-on and mid-off up, Symonds takes up the challenge. Runs down the track to lift it over long-on. Game on! Mid-on and mid-off still up in the circle
arm-ball, just outside off, cut to deep point
almost dragged back to the stumps. Sweeps from outside off, gets an inside-edge that takes the ball past the stumps, to short fine-leg
in the zone outside off, left alone
on the hips, glanced away fine. A six in the previous over and now a four. Symonds is off and running.
Bond goes for his throat, Symonds sways away quickly.
Now guns for the head. around 89 mph. Symonds duck under
Again the bouncer but  bit too high. Wide called.
slower one, 120 kmph delivery, full on the middle and leg, pushed to midwicket
142.2 kmph yorker, on the middle and off, dug out to Vettori at mid-off. Symonds is bit late in responding to Hussey's call but gets across in time.
turns in from outside off, slightly short in length, Hussey goes back to turn it behind square.
tossed-up, on the off stump line, Symonds leans forward to dead-bat it away
Aha! the slog-sweep is out. Flighted-up on the middle, turns away but Symonds carts it over midwicket
arm-ball, outside the off stump, full in length, Symonds tries to cut, gets an outside edge to short thirdman. too full to cut.

Hamish Marshall dazzles with a direct hit. Symonds pushes a length-delivery to point, Marshall swoops in and fires a throw at the striker's end but Hussey is in. Just in time. The decision is refered upstairs. Not out.
spins from middle and off stump line, Hussey stays back, works it to the on side
from round the stumps, overpitched, drilled through cover. Easy pickings.
Hussey goes for a wild-pull but doesn't connect.  Length-delivery that came in with the angle around the offstump line
full and outside off, square-driven to right of the man at deep cover
more rubbish from Franklin. short and wide outside off, Symonds tries to cut but can't reach it
fuller and closer to the off stump, Symonds goes back and across, and chops it fine, down to thirdman region
straight to thirdman this time.
Hussey is intent on pulling Franklin. Again the result is not satisfactory. Shovels it around to midwicket.
flighted delivery, ends up a low dipping full-toss, nudged around to square-leg, McCullum gives the chase but they complete the second run
tossed up outside off, driven down the ground, to long-off&
full and outside off, creamed past cover.
Vettori continues to flight. Dips in front of middle, Symonds pushes it to long-on
on a length, just outside off, cut late, with the spin.
comes in with the angle, on the middle and off, worked to midwicket
outside off stump, on a length, dabbed away to thirdman
on the middle, worked to midwicket
full toss, outside the off stump, powered down the ground
comes down the track, Vettori holds back the length, Hussey adjusts to push forward in defense.
spears in full and on the middle, Symonds ends up digging it out back to the bowler
Wonderful exhibition of running between the wickets. Just nudged to the square-leg region, very well placed, and they get two
almost holed up to cover. Too early into his drive and it just fell short of the waiting palms
in the channel outside off, dabbed down to thirdman
on the middle, no angle to work with, pushed back down the track
just outside off, punched to long-off
goes for a yorker, swing in late, dug out to long-on. Good stuff from Astle.
Another single as Hussey pings the long-off

almost had him lbw. Inside-edge saves Symonds. Nipped back slightly after landing on a length around the off stump line, Symonds is caught in two minds, whether to press forward or back, ends up hanging his bat out in defense

As it happens, a change, a not-so-flash delivery gets a wicket. Franklin, off a short run-up, sends across a four-ball. Short in length, well outside the off stump but Hussey ends up cutting straight to point
fuller and outside the offstump, Clarke eases forward to push it to cover

Franklin is grinning. He has just bowled a damn good delivery. Delivered from round the stumps, on a length, holds its line, Clarke ends up pushing inside the line. Fleming is impressed, moves in a slip
in the channel around off stump line, pushed to the offside. No chance of a run
And again. Length-delivery around off stump line, pushed to point. It's a wicket-maiden from Franklin.
full and just outside off, driven to left of long-off where Bond makes the stop. Can't prevent a second run though.
slightly slower, on the middle, Symonds lets it come to him, drops his wrists to place the ball close on the on side to get a single. Well played.
lunges forward to a length-delivery, pushes it to right of point and sets off for a quick run
presents the full-face of the bat in defense. He is on 49.
brings up his 20th ODI fifty and  3rd fifty against New Zealand, with a drive to long-off.
backs away to drill a full-length delivery to deep cover
tip and run. Pushes a length-delivery to the off side and sets off for a run. Symonds back on strike
drifting in on the pads, creamed past midwicket. Just a single though.
just outside the offstump, Symonds goes back and across and chops it down to thirdman
Another easy single. Fleming has the boundaries manned, not too many inside the ring at this stage. Clarke drops the ball close on the off side and jogs across for a run
Beaten outside off. An in-dipper and Clarke ends up driving outside the line. Surprised by the movement.
just outside the offstump, pushed past point
Symonds is beaten outside off as he attempts to cut a length-delivery fine but doesn't connect.
Clarke backs away to the leg side, Oram pushes it full outside off, Clarke reaches out for it and sends it towards cover.
Again can't get much force behind the shot. Shovels a full delivery on the offstump line to cover, will get a single
Clarke brings back Symonds on strike with a push past point. Oram from point gave the chase, and fired in a accurate throw to prevent the second run
Symonds goes for the jugular. Hurls himself down the track and throws his bat at a length-delivery outside off. Misses.
on the legs, full in length, worked past midwicket.
Again Symonds backs away, Franklin pings it short,  and Symonds drops down his wrists, sways away
Dropped by Vincent. Very tough chance at cover. It was full-blooded drive and  he dived to his right but couldn't cling on to the rising ball.
Backs away to slap a short-delivery to left of deep point where Oram makes the stop
Banged in short, outside the offstump, Symonds had backed away to the leg side and watches the ball sail through to the wicketkeeper

The legstump is pegged back! Attempted yorker turns into a low full-toss and Symonds shuffles across to the offstump in an attempt to tickle it fine. Misses and the ball brushes the pads before crashing into the leg stump. Big wicket for New Zealand. Symonds could have hurt them in these end-overs
length-delivery on the middle, pushed back down the track
full and on the legs, Lee lets it come to him, wrists it past square-leg
on a length, outside off, pushed to Hamish Marshall at point. No chance of a run. Clarke remains on strike.
on the off and middle, Clarke respects the line and the length and pushes it to cover
Clarke backs away to the legside, Mills tries to follow him but ends up pushing it down the legside. McCullem palms it away.
on the leg and middle, tickled behind square-leg
fine-leg was in and Mills gift-wraps a full toss on the legs, Clarke accepts.
Typical end-overs dismissal. Clarke threw his bat at a length-delivery, intending it to sail down the ground, but the moody-ball chose to fly down the throat of thirdman
on the off stump line, dabbed down to thirdman. Lee on strike.
Lee is cleaned up. Goes for the across-the-line slog, misses and hears the death knell. New Zealand are doing pretty well in these end-overs. Not allowing Australia to get away
Length-delivery, outside offstump, pushed to right of thirdman and they run hard to complete the second run
Bond pings Bracken's ribs. Pushed away to point.

And again. Bracken somehow manages to fend it off to the leg side and thinks that achievement needs to be celebrated with a single. Sets off for a suicidal run, a direct hit would have got another wicket for New Zealand
outside off, run down to thirdman

Now Mills goes for the throat-ball. Johnson takes his eyes off, ducks, and it thuds in to the shoulder and drops close on the offside. Again Bracken thinks there is a single in it, Johnson doesn't agree this time.
in the zone outside off, Johnson tries to steer it to thirdman but doesn't make contact
Another bouncer. Weak pull shot attempted, no contact.
length delvery on the middle, swatted past midwicket. Useful shot.
Wah! Bracken pulls off a fore-handed freaky shot over long-on!  It was a bouncer  and Bracken backed away to the leg side, and somehow middled his swat-pull and saw it sailing over the ropes.
again he backs away, this time Bond tries to ping the blockhole, the bat comes down in a hurry, gets an outside edge to thirdman
in the zone outside off, Johnson is beaten
Johnson tries to steal a run but Bond is too quick for him. Moves across to his right, picks up the ball, turns and fires in a direct hit at the non-striker's end
Lemon-cut to fine-leg fence. The good old inside-edge. Full and straight on the middle, bat comes down in a angle perfected by tailenders for years, and the ball evades the stumps.

inn2.comm: bang on target, a full-length delivery on the stumps, Vincent is forced to defend
full on the stumps, pushed back to Lee
good delivery lands a fraction outside off stump and kicks past Vincent's back-foot waft
lands halfway down the track and slips down leg, Gilchrist dives but doesnt field cleanly
full and wide of him, and he chooses to leave it go
good length on the stumps, Fleming takes the bottom hands off it as he defends to cover
full outside off stump, left alone again
full outside the off stump, some lateral movement off the pitch, Vincent judges it and shoulders arms
identical delivery, ball jags off the seam, again Vincent shoulders arms
this lands outside off stump and comes in, Vincent's rapped on the front leg but umpire Bucknor says no stroke offered, and that's going over leg stump
bad ball, far too wide of off stump, up go Bucknor's arms
typical McGrath channel outside off stump, probing, asking the batsman to play at it but Vincent resists once more
this time moves it in an inch and succeeds in getting Vincent to prod forward, and as planned the ball swishes past the outer edge, well  bowled
relatively straightforward ball outside off stump, Vincent hurries to get over it and smother any movement
short ball outside off stump, left alone by Fleming
good stuff, bowled at a good pace outside off stump, draws Fleming into the stand-and-hang-bat-out routine, and misses shaving the edge
more into middle and leg, Fleming comes forward and defends, ball pops up in front of midwicket and Fleming decides to pinch a single and get off the mark
good movement from outside off stump, cuts in a foot and beats Vincent's premeditated back-foot waft
good ball, moves into him and Vincent's caught on the pad, but the ball was carrying down leg
good ball on the off stump, and its well played by Vincent who keeps bat and pad together this time
moves this across him from middle and off, he leaves it alone
similar ball moves across him, but its well left by Fleming
another fullish delivery landing outside off stump is left alone
good ball on the stumps, defended by Fleming
strays onto leg stump and he clips that down to fine leg for four
short and wide, Fleming rocks back and cuts uppishly, gets a thicl edge but luckily for him its between second slip and gully and he picks up runs down to third man
full on middle and leg, tucked to midwicket for one
lands outside off and moves too much, wide called by Koertzen
middle and off line, Fleming drops the hands on that one as he looks for a sharp single in front of point, but wisely decides against it
full in the blockhole and well dug out by Fleming
short and wide outside off stump, this time Fleming leaves it alone
good ball outside off stump, Fleming squeezes that in the gap at gully for one down to third man
good ball that cuts in from off stump and raps Vincent's pad as he goes forward, clearly going down leg
full ball lands outside off stump and carries into Gilchrist's gloves, Fleming left that alone
nips into him from middle and leg, movement off the pitch, Fleming taps that in front of cover for the single

gone, simple as can be! Lands the ball on the money outside off stump, Vincent comes forward and pokes, head is going towards mid-off, eyes are elsewhere, the face of the bat is opened and the result is a simple edge to Ponting at second slip and Vincent's woeful tournament continues
good ball first up, fullish outside off stump and he gets forward and defends
angled wide of off stump and Astle shoulders arms
full and seaming away outside off stump, Astle hops forward and pokes at it, but gets beaten, fine over from McGrath...wonder how many times we've all seen that type of dismissal?
short and wide, Fleming tries to reach it but cant, wide called
on a good length outside off stump, Fleming is not to the pitch of it but follows through with the drive, played on the up but in the gap, they run hard for three

cleaned him up! Fast and furious outside the off stump on a great length, nips in a long way and Astle, who's feet go nowhere, can only poke at that and look on in horror as his middle stump goes for a walk, indecisive footwork didnt help, and well bowled Lee
good length on off stump, Marshall hops and defends to leg
full outside off stump, down onto one knee goes Marshall as he tries a square drive, but bat came down late
lands on a good length and moves in, back and across goes Marshall as he defends back to Lee
full outside off stump, Marshall gets forward and pushes that in the gap at cover and Symonds gives chase, just the single to get off  the mark
a good length outside off stump, Fleming has nothing to do with it, good over from Lee
bounced down the leg, Marshall ducks out of danger
full ball comes into him, Marshall times that well and drives past Bracken at mid-on for a brace
lands on a length and comes into him, Marshall covers his off stump in a jiffy and defends that down into the off side
too far outside off stump and too much swing, another wide given up by Australia
good movement off the surface outside off stump, Marshall negotiates the length and shoulders arms
short and wide, Marshall stands and tries the uppercut, ball bounces down to Mitchell Johnson sliding on the third man ropes
comes into him from middle and leg, Fleming's caught on the hop, Marshall tries for the legbye and manages despite a sharp throw from square leg
from around the wicket this time, angled into Fleming, who coolly defends to point with soft hands
tries a bouncer outside off stump, no danger for Fleming, who says naah, mate, I wont chase those
moves into him, some extra bounce hustles Fleming but he plays that late and keeps it down to fine leg, intelligently played
pitches on a good length on off stump, Marshall gets behind the ball and defends
short this time but Marshall cant time the cut well, nearly chops onto the off stump, room wasnt really there for an expansive cut
full and fast outside off stump, swings farther away and Rudi K calls it wide
back of a good length outside off stump, he rocks back and pushes into the covers, calls for the single and gets it to keep strike
moves in from that sweet spot outside off stump, defended into the covers

all over! I saw this one coming; Marshall just stands and dabs the bat at a wide delivery outside the off stump, and its a regulation edge into Gilchrist's palms, McGrath gets another, its back to the hut for that kid
good, short ball outside off stump, welcome, welcome says McGrath and Fulton quickly drops the wrists to get out of harm's way
McGrath rolls the fingers over that one, lands outside off stump and moves in but Fulton knows where his off stump is and leaves it alone
this one lands outside off stump and goes the other way, Fulton hops and awkwardly decides against a shot
good ball outside off stump lifts as Fulton pulls the bat out of the way, quality over that from McG
a good length outside off stump, left alone by Fleming
delivered from wide of the crease, too full and far away and Fleming shoulders arms
thats too far and swinging away, surprised it wasn't called wide

Well bowled! A fullish length outside off stump, after moving his way wider and wider with the previous deliveries Bracken brings one in closer and draws Fleming into the drive and then gets the ball to curl away exaggeratedly, and its a simple thick edge into Ponting's safe hands at second slip
full outside off again, left alone
full again and he leaves it alone
lands this one on a sweet length outside off stump, draws him forward and then shapes it away, beaten
Fulton's clueless as he hangs the bat out at a short ball outside off stump, I take back my statement about him knowing where his off stump is
lands outside off stump and jags in, catches him on the hop
lands on middle and leg and moves into Fulton, who hops and gets rapped on the leg, McGrath's got his number
full and wide, Fulton unleashes an airy square drive that doesnt carry to Clarke at point, uppishly played, a close call
lands on off stump and comes into Oram, who stands and keeps that out
lands on middle and leg and moves in, Fulton stands and gets an inside edge to square leg
lands on leg stump and hurries him into a weak hop, ball clips the pads and runs fine
lands outside off stump and moves away, Oram leaves it
full outside off stump and moving in considerably, Oram decides to leave it alone
lands outside off and goes the other way this time, Oram takes the bottom hand off the bat and withdraws
lands outside off and moves away, forces Oram to play at that and he gets a thick edge down to Johnson at third man
lands outside off stump and moves away, Oram shoulders arms
short ball on middle and leg, Oram moves away but gets smacked on the helmet
lands on a good length and Fulton goes back and defends, too much of defensive mode here

yeah, he has NO idea where his off stump is! Lands on a good length outside off stump and moves in, Fulton shoulders arms of all things and looks back to see his off stump pegged back!  Wasnt even a deadly delivery or anything, just a basic error on Fulton's part. McGrath gets a third!
good ball first-up, lands outside off and draws him into a tame prod
short and wide, McCullum chases it and gets a thick edge down to third man
lands on leg stump and raps the pads, Bracken shouts but that was carrying on too high
Gone! A fullish ball on middle and leg, McCullum tries to work that over mid-on, ball bobs up and Martyn takes a good catch moving to his right, Bracken gets another
good ball on the stumps, pushed to cover
too far away, wide called
full outside off stump, left alone
full outside off stump again, Vettori drives and gets beaten by the movement
drifts to middle and leg, Vettori plays that well in the gap at midwicket and gets off the mark
lands on a good length outside off stump and moves away, he shoulders arms
full outside off stump, left alone
good ball outside off, Vettori covers his off stump - thankfully - and allows it to pass
good ball on the stumps, defended with tight technique to mid-off
a fraction wider this time, Vettori chops that to Clarke on the move at point
dragged in short, but Vettori's pull into the ground cant beat Watson at midwicket
full on off stump, worked to midwicket with a call of 'WAIT' back to his partner
rapped on the legs as he attempts to flick, they pinch a run
full outside off stump, left alone
full outside off stump, squeezed past gully down to third man
full outside off stump, driven to Johnson at mid-off
full outside off stump, Oram flays the bat at that but fails to reach it, wide called
full in the zone, driven back in the air over Bracken's head down to long-off
full outside off stump, driven to mid-off
full again, defended
comes onto him quickly, he comes forward and defends, gets an inside edge
full again, he drives to covers
full once more, he leaves this alone
lands on middle and leg and its worked to square leg for one
full on off stump, Vettori defends back to the bowler
full again, draws him into a leaden-footed drive and the thick edge lands just in front of Ponting at second slip, lucky for him
lands outside off stump and seams away past his backfoot prod
dropped! Full and wide, Vettori flays the bat at it and Hussey drops a sitter at first slip, in and out of his hands
full on the pads, flicked imperiously over square leg for four, top shot
full and wide outside off stump, he shoulders arms to this one
lands outside off and moves away, Vettori is beaten on the backfoot as he prods
this one comes in and Vettori's again beaten on the backfoot chop, well bowled
full this time and Vettori gets to the pitch and drives to mid-off, well played
short and moving into him, Vettori chops the late cut past Ponting at second slip and picks up four, streaky but effective
this lands outside off stump and jags into him and he runs that past point
he moves to over the wicket and fires in the yorker, well bowled and well dug out
full and fast outside off stump, Vettori leaves it alone
wider outside off stump, again Vettori leaves it alone
identical delivery, and Vettori shoulders arms with a stride forward
this one moves into him as its much closer to off stump, Vettori drives in the air towards mid-off and finds the gap
angled into middle and leg, worked straight to Watson at midwicket
lands wide of off stump, Vettori plays and misses
strives for the yorker but ends up a low full toss, Vettori punches wide of mid-off
good ball outside off stump, left alone
short and he swivels on the pull through square leg
lands on a great length outside off stump and whizzes past Oram's backfoot prod
shortish around off stump, Oram defends and runs that down to third man where Lee dives well and stops the four
lands outside off stump and carries to Gilchrist at a good height as Oram leaves it alone
too short and drifting down leg, he attempts to smash that off the hips but its called wide anyways
drifts to middle and leg, moving down, and he flicks that superbly in the gap at midwicket, a simple roll of the wrists against the pace of the ball, and picks up four, well played
lands outside off stump and seams past Vettori's backfoot waft
fuller this time, in a good channel, Vettori plays that late into the covers
drifts to leg stump and Vettori clips that well past square leg to get four, good cricketing sense shown by a gritty customer

full outside off stump, Vettori plants the front foot forward and drives in the air past mid-off, Martyn gives chase and pulls that back in with a fine dive on the ropes, just flicks that in as he himself goes over
immense! Full in the zone and Oram punches that dead straight between Vettori and the stumps and the ball scorches down to the ropes, fine as they come
oh ho! Full outside off stump and Oram frees the arms, simply picks that up over mid-off and doesnt even bother to run, expensive over this for Australia
lands outside off stump and nips in sharply, ball gets tangled in Vettori's pads somewhere, ahh its between his legs and he removes it and drops it at his feet
full on the stumps and its defended back to Johnson
he bangs in the bouncer and Vettori ducks down onto his haunches
full outside off stump, he gets to the pitch and drives to Martyn at mid-off for one
lands on middle and leg and he works that in the gap at square leg
short and wide, he chops the cut into the ground in front of Clarke at point
full on off stump, worked to square leg
comes into him, he hops and works that to midwicket for one
wide of off stump, Vettori shoulders arms
short and rising outside off stump, Oram was in two minds, looked to leave it alone and gets an edge down to third man
full on off stump, he goes back and works that in the gap at midwicket for one more
full outside off stump, driven to cover
full-length delivery, angling in from the offstump line, Vettori stabs at it, and gets a single behind square-leg
banged in short, and Oram was caught in bit of tangle as he expected the ball to climb more than it did - ended up just above waist-high - but adjusted to push it away to the offside
length-delivery, coming in with the angle, Oram pokes at it, gets an inside edge ... ball drops near the stumps
gets off the strike with a nudged-single to the on side
on the offstump line, slanting in, pushed to cover
Firmly punched down the ground.Vettori continues to fight. In the slot, Vettori leant forward and presented the full face of the bat.
short of length, on the off, punched on the up to cover
full and drifting onto the legs, flicked past midwicket. 100 up for New Zealand. The fightback continues.
aims  for the blockhole, driven to cover
Oh ho! heave over midwicket. Didn't quite get hold of it but should have been two but Oram slips at the non-strikers end. Blame the dew.
on a length, around the off stump line, pushed to point
pushes it down the leg side. wide called.
hit the deck around short of length, just outside the offstump, punched to short cover
much fuller, on the off and middle, Oram is caught a bit at the crease, ends up pushing his bat out in a hurry, gets a single on the on side
Lovely dab to thirdman. Ala Arjuna Ranatunga. He let the slightly short-of-length delivery to come to him, opened the bat-face and ran it down fine.
length-delivery, coming in from outside the offstump, Vettori doesn't quite find the room to dab it fine, ends up steering to backward point
manages to dab it to thirdman this time. This delivery remained just outside off, giving him room to cut fine
on the legs, kept a touch low, Oram tries to flick it away, doesn't connect and it rolls off the pads
slanted delivery, just outside off, run down to thirdman
on the hips, another failed flick shot, another leg bye.
on the middle and off, full in length, Vettori taps it close on the off side, to right of short cover and runs with the stroke.&
Watson likes his bouncers. I wonder whether he likes them at discotheques too. First bouncer of the night - won't be the last-  and Oram ducks under
just outside offstump, short in length, punched to cover
slower ball, delivered like an offbreak, full in length, steered to point
short of length, on the middle, pulled over midwicket.  Will the Australians start to worry now?!
short of length, outside the offstump, cut to deep point.
pushed towards mid-off and runs with the stroke. The singles keep coming.
bit of room outside the offstump, slashed to thirdman
length-delivery, just outside the offstump, Vettori again shapes to run it down to thirdman, but can't beat the widish slip.
will retain the strike with a nudge to mid-on
back of length, slanting away, steered to backward point. Vettori stays adjacent to the line of the ball, doesn't quite come behind it and that allows him to ping thirdman repeatedly
There he goes again. Just outside the off stump, Vettori stays beside the line rather than behind and runs it down real fine. Watson makes a valiant attempt but the sliding takes him beyond the ropes
floated on the off, pushed to cover point
tossed up outside off, Oram takes the aerial route, drives over cover
slightly short and cut to deep point
runs down the track, Symonds hurls in a low full-toss, swatted away, not much force behind it and Hogg, at midwicket, moves to his left to make a smart stop
hit the deck around short of length, on the hips, tucked away to fine-leg
fuller, on the middle and leg, driven to mid-on
Opts for a bouncer again. Oram Sways away.

Almost caught by Clarke at backward point. He is not sure whether he has taken it clearly. Just brushed the ground as he tries to scoop it up. Oram had slashed a back-of-length delivery and Clarke threw himself forward but couldn't get his fingers under it completely. He indicated rightaway that he was not sure.
Vettori shuffles across to tap a delivery on the middle and leg to fine-leg
goes for a sweep shot but doesn't connect
full and outside off, square-driven to deep point
from round the stumps, floated in on the middle, full in length, driven to long-on. Brings Vettori on strike. He is on 49
Very slow through the air, well flighted as well, outside the offstump, tapped to short thirdman, Vettori wants a run but is sent back
Vettori brings up his 3rd ODI fifty with a pick-up shot towards long-off. Well played Sir.
pings the ribs, Vettori is cramped but manages to stab it away to the offside. Oram calls him over for a quick single
Dangerous tame push by Oram. Bit early into his shot, he just pushed at a length-delivery and sent it in the air, one bounce to right of mid-off

Now Vettori almost drags one back into the stumps. Gilchrist dives to his right to save five runs - it was heading straight for the helmet placed behind him.  It was full-length delivery just outside off and Vettori again tried to ping the fine thirdman fence. Gilchrist had moved to his left and then had to change directions
kicks up from a length, tapped deliberately over the wide slip, down to thirdman
on the hips, tucked behind square-leg

Huge breakthrough. Symonds and Gilchrist combo works perfectly for Australia. Very smark work from Gilchrist. Symonds beat Oram in flight and then by the turn off the track. Oram was sucked forward, his back feet dragged outside the crease and as soon as he realised he was had, he tried to plant the feet inside the crease but Gilchrist had quickly whipped off the bails. Just in time. It was very good fighting knock from Oram and his dismissal would hurt New Zealand
overpitched outside off, driven to deep cover
driven to long-on
full, dipping in front of middle and off, goes inside-out to find deep cover
very full, on the off, Vettori shuffles across and sweeps it behind square-leg
angling away, kept a touch low, Vettori tries to run it down to thirdman but doesn't connect
around the offstump line, slanting away, Vettori stays beside the line, pushes it to cover
pings the thirdman again. He has done it repeatedly this evening. Any room outside the offstump he dabs it fine. If short , like how this delivery was, he slashes it in the air over the widish slip.
just outside the offstump, steered to point
from round the stumps, slow through the air, floated in around the middle, driven to long-on
Symonds gifts a boundary. Sends across a full toss, must be the dew, and spanked to deep midwicket
tip and run. Pushed to right of cover and off they go.
And again Vettori pings the thirdman fence. Delicate late-cut .
Now the sweep shot. Swept in front of square
in the zone outside off, on a length, steered straight to backward point
ducks under a bouncer. 84 from 70
on the hips, swatted away past square-leg
outside off, angling away, cut to first of those two men.. Ponting.
Now he shuffles across outside the offstump to work a length-delivery on the off to fine-leg!
Watson strikes for Australia. Franklin tries to take inspiration from Vettori and attempts to run a length-delivery outside off to thirdman but gets a faint nick.
full, flat and on the off, driven to long-off
slow through the air, turns in from outside off, worked to midwicket
tosses this one up, outside off, driven to cover where Mitchell Johnson makes a half-stop diving to his left

The sweep hasn't been working as well as the late-cut for Vettori. Top-edges it behind square-leg, Watson running in from long-leg is almost beaten by the turn of the ball after landing but adjusts to make a diving stop.
just outside off, Vettori tries to send it down to thirdman but Ponting inside the circle - one of the two men behind point, within the 30-yard circle- cuts if off.
full, driven straight but Watson makes a good stop
Vettori kills an extremely slower one.  Waited for a long time for it to arrive before slapping it past midwicket
length-delivery, around the offstump, pushed to cover

Slightly short of length, on the leg and middle, Vettori opens up his stance by taking the right leg outside the line and pulls it over midwicket. There is a huge gap there. Vettori continues to grit it out.
banged in short, it rises chest-high, dabbed to the offside
floated outside off, pushed to cover
turns in from outside off, Mills tries to work it to on side, doesn't connect and the ball runs off the pads to short thirdman

Almost a run out but bad throw from the deep saves Vettori. Swept from outside offstump and Watson, running in from long-leg,  had a shy at the non striker's end but Symonds coudn't grab the half-volley. It landed at a awkward length in front of him...
yorker-length on the middle, dug out to mid-on
fires in a yorker straight-up, ends up as a low full-toss around the offstump, swatted to mid-on
Symonds misses a throw. Again Vettori has a lucky escape.  Pushed to midwicket and they run with the stroke. Vettori had given up half-way but Symonds misses.

A tired Vettori falls. Australia heave a sigh of relief. Vettori, getting increasingly tired as the innings progressed, backed away outside the leg stump and had a go at a fullish delivery that followed him but the ball rebounded off his pads back on to the stumps.
yorker turns into low full-toss, pushed to point
banged in short, Bond pokes at it, misses.
full, driven to long-on
short and outside off, cut past point
tossed up full, Mills drills it straight over Symonds head. Symonds wondered whether it would be wise to put a hand up to catch but chooses not to. Wise decision as it was drilled very powerfully,
Aha! heaved over deep midwicket. RIght in the slot, he swings it with the turn. New Zealand continue to fight
full, just outside the offstump, sliced to point
kicks up from back of length, Bond tries to cut but is beaten by the extra bounce.
Wah! Bond backs away to drill a full-length delivery over extra cover. Well-pitched up and smoked over cover. 41 from 32
Johnson bangs it in, Bond goes for a cut, can't connect though.
speared in full, driven back down the track, Johnson stops it and fires it back at the striker's end, Bond tries to get out the way but is hit flush on the boot. Hurt him a bit there.
Mills gives him the charge, throws his bat at a short of length delivery, intending to send it over deep midwicket, misses. Lee won't be amused.
Lee will be bemused now. Mills backed away this time and carved a short delivery past mid-off. Now mid-off goes back and fine-leg is up.
Mills backs away again, Lee follows him to cramp him up. Just pushed back down the track
Again Mills backs away, to fore-hand slap a short-of-length delivery through mid-off, down to the man at the deep.
Bond gets Mills back on strike with a push to left of Symonds at cover.
That'd it. Australia make an entry into the final of Champions Trophy for the first time. Lee bangs one short, Mills backs away, again, to attempt a slog but gets a top-edge.
